description.narrative: UNICEF-supported efforts in youth development and violence prevention programmes to build non-violent relationships empowered over 2,000 young people living in volatile communities, and therapeutic interventions to cope with trauma reached another 2,000 children. Social and behaviour change communication interventions were initiated to promote positive parenting and the elimination of VAC, reaching more than 450 parents/caregivers living in volatile communities. UNICEF also strengthened the institutional capacity of the National Parenting Support Commission, a government agency that reached 117,000 parents through various parenting interventions in 2019. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:16/12/2019
